  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "1998-05-22", 
    "text": "Ticket Scalping Reduction Act of 1998 - Amends the Federal criminal code to prohibit, and set penalties for, using the mails or any facility of interstate or foreign commerce to scalp five or more tickets in a single transaction. Defines \"scalp\" as to resell, or offer to resell, a ticket at a markup of more than $5 or ten percent of its face value."
